2500|$|On the field, Baloo played cricket as an equal, but off it he was {{segregated}} {{from the}} Europeans {{and the higher}} caste Hindus during rest and meal breaks. While his teammates dined inside the pavilion on fine china, Baloo was left outside <b>to</b> <b>eat</b> <b>and</b> <b>drink</b> out of disposable clay crockery. Despite this treatment, he bowled well and took plenty of wickets, leading his club to several victories almost single handedly.(Guha 2002:93) ...|$|E
